 when renewing your motorcycle documents.</p><hr data-start="2531" data-end="2534" /><h2 data-start="2536" data-end="2608"><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit;">Which motorcycle insurance is the cheapest in Malaysia?</span></h2><p data-start="2672" data-end="2955">The cheapest motorcycle insurance is usually <em data-start="2717" data-end="2730">Third Party</em> coverage, as it only protects against damage or injury you cause to others. Comprehensive coverage costs more but includes your own motorcycle. Premiums also depend on your bike’s CC, age, and your No Claim Discount (NCD).</p><h3 data-start="2957" data-end="3005">Is motor insurance compulsory in Malaysia?</h3><p data-start="3006" data-end="3210">Yes. Under Malaysian law, all vehicles including motorcycles must have at least <em data-start="3086" data-end="3099">Third Party</em> insurance before you can renew your road tax. Riding without insurance is illegal and can lead to penalties.</p><h3 data-start="3212" data-end="3270">Which insurance company is the cheapest in Malaysia?</h3><p data-start="3271" data-end="3514">There isn’t a single cheapest company for everyone, since premiums vary by bike type and rider profile. Popular insurers include Allianz, Zurich, Etiqa, Takaful Ikhlas, Berjaya Sompo, and MyEG. Always compare quotes before making a decision.</p><h3 data-start="3516" data-end="3564">Which motor insurance is best in Malaysia?</h3><p data-start="3565" data-end="3796">The best insurance depends on your needs. If you want the lowest cost, Third Party is best. For peace of mind and full protection, Comprehensive is better. Some riders prefer insurers with fast claims and strong customer service.</p><h3 data-start="3798" data-end="3835">How much NCD do I get per year?</h3><p data-start="3836" data-end="3954">For motorcycles in Malaysia, the NCD increases every year you ride claim-free, up to a maximum of 25% after 5 years:</p><ul data-start="3955" data-end="4013"><li data-start="3955" data-end="3969"><p data-start="3957" data-end="3969">Year 1: 0%</p></li><li data-start="3970" data-end="3985"><p data-start="3972" data-end="3985">Year 2: 15%</p></li><li data-start="3986" data-end="4013"><p data-start="3988" data-end="4013">Year 3–5: 25% (maximum)</p></li></ul><h3 data-start="4015" data-end="4065">Can I transfer my NCD to another motorcycle?</h3><p data-start="4066" data-end="4220">Yes, you can transfer your NCD when you buy a new motorcycle, but it must remain under the same name. You can’t share NCD across two active motorcycles.</p><h3 data-start="4222" data-end="4278">Can I transfer my NCD to my wife or family member?</h3><p data-start="4279" data-end="4393">No. NCD cannot be transferred to another person, even a spouse. It belongs to the policyholder, not the vehicle.</p><h3 data-start="4395" data-end="4435">How do I check my NCD in Malaysia?</h3><p data-start="4436" data-end="4614">You can check your current NCD with your insurer, via MyEG, or through the PIAM (Persatuan Insurans Am Malaysia) NCD database. Some insurers also provide an NCD checker online.</p><h3 data-start="4616" data-end="4670">Which motorcycle insurance coverage is the best?</h3><p data-start="4671" data-end="4864">Comprehensive coverage is the best for full protection, as it covers your motorcycle against theft, fire, accidents, and third-party liability. Highly recommended for new or high-value bikes.</p><h3 data-start="4866" data-end="4926">How do I get cheaper motorcycle insurance in Malaysia?</h3><ul data-start="4927" data-end="5142"><li data-start="4927" data-end="4979"><p data-start="4929" data-end="4979">Keep a clean riding record to maintain your NCD.</p></li><li data-start="4980" data-end="5046"><p data-start="4982" data-end="5046">Choose a lower coverage plan (Third Party if budget is tight).</p></li><li data-start="5047" data-end="5089"><p data-start="5049" data-end="5089">Compare quotes from multiple insurers.</p></li><li data-start="5090" data-end="5142"><p data-start="5092" data-end="5142">Skip unnecessary add-ons if you don’t need them.</p></li></ul><div><h2 data-start="955" data-end="995">Why Combine Road Tax and Insurance?</h2><p data-start="996" data-end="1155">Most riders in Malaysia need to renew both insurance and road tax at the same time. By using our calculator, you don’t need two separate tools – you’ll know:</p><ul data-start="1156" data-end="1318"><li data-start="1156" data-end="1212"><p data-start="1158" data-end="1212"><strong data-start="1158" data-end="1179">Insurance Premium</strong> (Third Party or Comprehensive)</p></li><li data-start="1213" data-end="1238"><p data-start="1215" data-end="1238"><strong data-start="1215" data-end="1236">Stamp Duty (RM10)</strong></p></li><li data-start="1239" data-end="1274"><p data-start="1241" data-end="1274"><strong data-start="1241" data-end="1272">Road Tax based on engine CC</strong></p></li><li data-start="1275" data-end="1318"><p data-start="1277" data-end="1318"><strong data-start="1277" data-end="1316">Total Amount (Insurance + Road Tax)</strong></p></li></ul><hr data-start="1320" data-end="1323" /><h2 data-start="1325" data-end="1379">Motorcycle Road Tax in Malaysia (Quick Reference)</h2><p data-start="1380" data-end="1465">Motorcycle road tax is generally affordable, but it increases with engine capacity:</p><ul data-start="1466" data-end="1615"><li data-start="1466" data-end="1493"><p data-start="1468" data-end="1493">Up to 150cc: RM2 – RM30</p></li><li data-start="1494" data-end="1525"><p data-start="1496" data-end="1525">151cc – 250cc: RM50 – RM100</p></li><li data-start="1526" data-end="1558"><p data-start="1528" data-end="1558">251cc – 500cc: RM150 – RM250</p></li><li data-start="1559" data-end="1591"><p data-start="1561" data-end="1591">501cc – 800cc: RM300 – RM400</p></li><li data-start="1592" data-end="1615"><p data-start="1594" data-end="1615">Above 800cc: RM500+</p></li></ul><p data-start="1617" data-end="1694">With our calculator, these amounts are a