 Malaysia, you must have valid motorcycle insurance before renewing road tax.</p><h3 data-start="2391" data-end="2440">Why is road tax different in East Malaysia?</h3><p data-start="2441" data-end="2526">Road tax in Sabah and Sarawak is generally cheaper compared to Peninsular Malaysia.</p><h3 data-start="2528" data-end="2572">Can I calculate car road tax here too?</h3><p data-start="2573" data-end="2729">This tool is focused on motorcycles. For cars, road tax is higher and depends on whether it’s a saloon (sedan/hatchback) or non-saloon (SUV, MPV, pickup).</p></div><hr data-start="5144" data-end="5147" /><p data-start="5149" data-end="5276"><em data-start="5149" data-end="5274">Disclaimer: This calculator provides estimates only. Please check with your insurance company for the exact premium amount.</em></p>","column_gap":{"unit":"px","size":0,"sizes":[]},"__globals__":{"text_color":"globals/colors?id=secondary"},"typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_family":"Roboto","typography_font_weight":"400","eael_vto_writing_gradient_color_repeater":[{"eael_vto_writing_gradient_color":"#7C62FF","eael_vto_writing_gradient_color_location":{"unit":"%","size":50},"_id":"98f3a8f"},{"eael_vto_writing_gradient_color":"#FF6464","eael_vto_writing_gradient_color_location":{"unit":"%","size":90},"_id":"de9f6ac"}],"eael_image_masking_custom_clip_path":"clip-path: polygon(50% 0%, 80% 10%, 100% 35%, 100% 70%, 80% 90%, 50% 100%, 20% 90%, 0% 70%, 0% 35%, 20% 10%);","eael_image_masking_custom_clip_path_hover":"clip-path: polygon(50% 0%, 80% 10%, 100% 35%, 100% 70%, 80% 90%, 50% 100%, 20% 90%, 0% 70%, 0% 35%, 20% 10%);"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false}]

