" />Yes. As of 2025, full exemption up to RM500k, and 50% exemption between RM500k – RM1m.</p><p data-start="5363" data-end="5597"><strong data-start="5363" data-end="5413">5. How do I calculate my eligibility manually?</strong><br data-start="5413" data-end="5416" />Add your monthly income, subtract commitments, apply DSR limit (usually 45%), then estimate your loan amount using bank interest &amp; tenure. Our calculator automates this instantly.</p><hr data-start="5599" data-end="5602" /><h2 data-start="5604" data-end="5621">✅ Final Word</h2><p data-start="5623" data-end="5853">Your <strong data-start="5628" data-end="5653">home loan eligibility</strong> depends on more than just salary. Banks look at your commitments, DSR, age, and credit history. Use this calculator to check your numbers before applying, so you can approach banks with confidence.</p><p data-start="5855" data-end="5984">👉 If you’re buying with a spouse, try our [<strong data-start="5899" data-end="5950">Joint Home Loan Eligibility Calculator Malaysia</strong>] for combined income scenarios.</p>","column_gap":{"unit":"px","size":0,"sizes":[]},"__globals__":{"text_color":"globals/colors?id=secondary"},"typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_family":"Roboto","typography_font_weight":"400"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false}]

