rong> may face stricter rules.</p></li><li data-start="1215" data-end="1315"><p data-start="1217" data-end="1315">Some banks require at least <strong data-start="1245" data-end="1277">6 months in your current job</strong> or <strong data-start="1281" data-end="1312">2 years in total employment</strong>.</p></li></ul><h3 data-start="1317" data-end="1339">3. <strong data-start="1324" data-end="1337">Age Range</strong></h3><ul data-start="1340" data-end="1473"><li data-start="1340" data-end="1393"><p data-start="1342" data-end="1393">Most banks set <strong data-start="1357" data-end="1374">21 – 60 years</strong> as the standard.</p></li><li data-start="1394" data-end="1473"><p data-start="1396" data-end="1473">Some extend to <strong data-start="1411" data-end="1423">65 years</strong> provided the loan is cleared before retirement.</p></li></ul><h3 data-start="1475" data-end="1503">4. <strong data-start="1482" data-end="1501">Credit Standing</strong></h3><ul data-start="1504" data-end="1715"><li data-start="1504" data-end="1548"><p data-start="1506" data-end="1548">CCRIS / CTOS reports are always checked.</p></li><li data-start="1549" data-end="1629"><p data-start="1551" data-end="1629">Any missed payments, overdue loans, or blacklisting will reduce eligibility.</p></li><li data-start="1630" data-end="1715"><p data-start="1632" data-end="1715">A clean repayment history strengthens your chances and may unlock lower interest.</p></li></ul><h3 data-start="1717" data-end="1752">5. <strong data-start="1724" data-end="1750">Debt Commitments (DSR)</strong></h3><ul data-start="1753" data-end="1936"><li data-start="1753" data-end="1858"><p data-start="1755" data-end="1858">Even if you meet income and age, your <strong data-start="1793" data-end="1815">Debt Service Ratio</strong> must stay within the <strong data-start="1837" data-end="1855">~60% guideline</strong>.</p></li><li data-start="1859" data-end="1936"><p data-start="1861" data-end="1936">Example: A RM4,000 salary means max RM2,400 can go to all loans combined.</p></li></ul><h3 data-start="1938" data-end="1964">6. <strong data-start="1945" data-end="1962">Other Factors</strong></h3><ul data-start="1965" data-end="2278"><li data-start="1965" data-end="2043"><p data-start="1967" data-end="2043"><strong data-start="1967" data-end="1983">Nationality:</strong> Most banks only approve Malaysian citizens or PR holders.</p></li><li data-start="2044" data-end="2165"><p data-start="2046" data-end="2165"><strong data-start="2046" data-end="2071">Loan Tenure &amp; Amount:</strong> Shorter tenure may increase approval chances since monthly instalments are more manageable.</p></li><li data-start="2166" data-end="2278"><p data-start="2168" data-end="2278"><strong data-start="2168" data-end="2193">Banking Relationship:</strong> Existing salary crediting or savings account with the same bank may help approval.</p></li></ul><h2 data-start="216" data-end="265"><br />💰 Personal Loan Calculator Based on Salary In Malaysia</h2><p data-start="267" data-end="449">Not sure how much you can actually borrow? Use the calculator with your <strong data-start="339" data-end="357">monthly income</strong> to estimate eligibility based on Malaysia’s common <strong data-start="409" data-end="446">60% DSR (Debt Service Ratio) rule</strong>.</p><ul data-start="451" data-end="941"><li data-start="451" data-end="509"><p data-start="453" data-end="509"><strong data-start="453" data-end="464">Step 1:</strong> Enter your monthly income (e.g., RM5,000).</p></li><li data-start="510" data-end="615"><p data-start="512" data-end="615"><strong data-start="512" data-end="523">Step 2:</strong> Calculator applies a 60% DSR cap → RM3,000 is the maximum allowed for all debts combined.</p></li><li data-start="616" data-end="723"><p data-start="618" data-end="723"><strong data-start="618" data-end="629">Step 3:</strong> If you already have car loan, housing loan, or credit card commitments, deduct those first.</p></li><li data-start="7